# VERYFI AUDIT REPORT

**Goal:** To identify errors in the current documentation and provide solutions to fix them

**Audited By**: Usoro, Amaeti Edet  
**Date**: May, 2025

**Audit Structure:** The audit report is divided into three main sections based on Verify's three main products, i.e., Data Abstraction API, Verify Lens For Mobile, and Veryfi Lens For Browser.

## DATA ABSTRACTION API

### Home Page

**Category:** Overview

**Issue:** There is no high-level overview of Veryfi and the services it offers.

**URL**: [https://docs.veryfi.com/](https://docs.veryfi.com/)

**Solution**: There should be an overview that briefly explains what Veryfi does and the services it offers.

**Example:** Veryfi is an AI-powered document tool that transforms unstructured documents in the form of receipts, invoices, checks, and other business documents into structured and actionable data in seconds.

Veyfi offers two main products, which are:

1\. Veryfi Optical Character Recognition (OCR) API: This is used for securely extracting data from different document types, such as receipts, checks, contracts, bank statements, W-2s, W-9s, and W-8BEN-E forms.

2\. Veryfi Lens: This is used for capturing documents on mobile and browser applications.  

**Impact**: Implementing this change in the documentation will help new users quickly have a basic understanding of Veryfi products and their functionalities. This can also help them determine if these functionalities suit their needs

**Priority**: High

###  Getting Started

**Issue i:** The information on how to start building with Veryfi is unclear.

**URL:** [https://docs.veryfi.com/\#getting-started](https://docs.veryfi.com/#getting-started)

**Solution**: There should be a clear guide on how to start building with any of Veryfi's products.  
**Example:** 

Getting Started

To start building with Veryfi products, follow these steps: 

Step 1: Create a [Veryfi account](https://app.veryfi.com/auth/register/?invite_code=api).

Step 2: Check the Veryfi OCR API [Authentication page](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/getting-started/authentication/) to get started with the Veryfi API for data extraction.

Step 3: Check the Veryfi Lens for Mobile [Authentication page](https://docs.veryfi.com/lens/mobile/introduction/authentification/) to get started with the Veryfi mobile SDK for document capturing on mobile applications.

Step 4: Check the Veryfi Lens for Browser [Quick Start page](https://docs.veryfi.com/lens/browser-v2/getting-started/quick/) to get started with the Veryfi browser lens SDK for document capturing on web applications.

**Priority**: High  
**Impact**: Implementing this can help developers quickly get started with any Veryfi products they want to use in their application

### Authentication Page

**Issue i**: The guide on how to get the required credentials and authorize API calls for the Veryfi OCR API is not clear, and there are no use of screenshots to guide developers.

**URL**: [https://docs.veryfi.com/api/getting-started/authentication/](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/getting-started/authentication/)

**Solution**: There should be a clear guide on how developers can obtain the required credentials and authorize their API calls.

**Example:**

Credentials

The Veryfi OCR API uses API keys to authenticate requests. To make a successful request, you need to get your API keys, Client ID, and username.

Follow these steps to get your credentials:

Step 1: Log in or sign up for a [Veryfi account](https://app.veryfi.com/auth/register/).

Step 2: Navigate to the ‘Settings’ section and select ‘keys.’

Step 3: Navigate to the ‘API key’ section to get your API keys.

Step 4: Navigate to the ‘Client ID’ section to get your client ID.

**Priority**: Intermediate

**Impact**: Implementing this can help developers easily get their credentials and kickstart their integration process.

**Issue ii:** The ‘Interactive API V8: Receipt and invoices’ link is broken..

![][image1]

**Solution**: The issue should be resolved by replacing it with a valid link

**Priority**: High

**Impact**: Rectifying this issue will enable developers to quickly navigate to the interactive API page and test API endpoints without setting up a testing environment.

**Issue iii:** The \`environment\_url\` is incorrectly spelled.

![][image2]

**Issue iv:** The documentation of each endpoint is not hyperlinked in the Environment URL section. This means developers need to search for the documentation of the endpoint they want to use.

![][image3]

**Solution iv**: The documentation of each endpoint should be hyperlinked, i.e., (Invoices & Receipts, Business Cards, Checks), for developers to easily access it, since it is a required parameter to make a successful request. 

**Impact**: Implementing this will enable developers to easily navigate to their desired endpoint and make a request to Veryfi.

**Priority**: Intermediate

### Receipts & Invoices

**Issue i:** The descriptions of most endpoints are too lengthy. Developers don’t need too much information. They only want to know how it works.

 **URL**: [https://docs.veryfi.com/api/receipts-invoices/process-a-document/](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/receipts-invoices/process-a-document/)

**Solution ii:** The description should be shortened, and a link to other information about that particular endpoint should be added to it in case developers want to learn more.

**Example**: \`Process a Document\` endpoint.

This endpoint allows you to submit and extract data from unstructured documents into valuable business insights. It enables you to submit supported file formats and retrieve extracted data in JSON format.   
For more information about the supported file formats and sizes, check this [page](https://faq.veryfi.com/en/articles/5415096-file-formats-veryfi-supports).

**Priority**: High

**Impact**: Implementing this change will enable developers to quickly know the functionality of an endpoint without bothering them with too much information.

**Issue ii:** No use of callouts to highlight important information for developers in the \`Bulk process Multiple Document\` description.

![][image5]

**URL**: https://docs.veryfi.com/api/receipts-invoices/bulk-process-multiple-documents/

**Solution ii**: There should be an ‘important note’ callout to catch the developer's attention to this information.

**Priority**: Low

### Business Cards

**Issue i:** The description for ‘Update a Business Card’ is lengthy.   
URL: [https://docs.veryfi.com/api/business-cards/update-a-business-card/](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/business-cards/update-a-business-card/)

**Solution**: The description should be shortened, and a link to other related information about that endpoint should be added in case developers want to learn more.

**Example:** 

This endpoint allows you to update a Document that Veryfi's Machine Learning models have already processed to ensure data extraction accuracy. This enables Veryfi's Machine Learning models to relearn the updated information, allowing them to stay accurate and up-to-date.

### Contracts

**Issue i:** There is no description for most of the endpoints in the ‘Contracts’ section.

**Example URLs:** [Get Contracts](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/contracts/get-contracts/), [Process a Contract](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/contracts/process-a-contract/), and [Get a Contract](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/contracts/get-a-contract/).

**Solution**: A concise description should be added for each endpoint to enable developers to know their functionalities.

### Data Abstraction General Issues

**Issue i:** All endpoints in the ‘Data Abstraction’ section are not logically arranged.

**Solution**: It is logical to place the ‘Get a Check,’ ‘Get Checks,’ and ‘Process a Check’ before the ‘Delete a Check’ endpoint. This applies to every other endpoint in the ‘Data Abstraction’ section.

**Priority**: Intermediate

**Issue ii:** Some endpoint descriptions are not clear.

**Example URLs**: [Get Contracts](%20https://docs.veryfi.com/api/contracts/get-contracts/,%20), [Process a Contract](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/contracts/process-a-contract/), and [Get W-2s](https://docs.veryfi.com/api/w2s/get-w-2-s/).

**Solution**: There should be a clear description of the functionality of each endpoint.

**Example**: Process a Contract

This endpoint allows you to process a contract.

**Priority:** Intermediate
